<br>
There is no calling in sick to work, there is showing up on time and heading over to sickcall so a doctor can certify that you are too sick to work that day.<br>
<br>
There is not showing up for work drunk off your tail, that's a fast ticket to the brig, shipmate. (yeah, I'm Navy, can you tell?)<br>
<br>
The military can and will push you to the limits of your abilities and beyond.  However, it does this by rebuilding your work ethic to something more team oriented.  If your brother does not work well with teams, then he should not waste his time or his recruiter's time.<br>
<br>
As for the different branches, Marines have the coolest fighting jobs and hence the biggest bragging rights.  The Navy won't stick you on the same remote base for ten years straight like the A.F., instead they will move  you every 2-4 years allowing you to see the world if you so like.  The Air Force does have the best bases but is also teased a lot for their &quot;cushy&quot; job structures.  Army has the most number of billets to fill with the least glamorous jobs so they make up for it with better educational benefits.<br>
<br>
A few final notes:  Navy has more airplanes that Air Force because they have more water to cover than Air Force has land to cover.  Army has more boats than Navy.  Navy of course has the most ships but the Marines and Army have virtually all the small shore landing crafts out there.  And no matter what service you go into, they will ALL send you overseas more than they send you stateside with the sole exception of the Coast Guard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lilybellefv>Lilybelle FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/24/03 8:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2032.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Military</span><hr size=1> Thank you all so much for your replies.  I'm going to forward your comments to him and I'm sure he'll get in touch with some of you.<br>
