weeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeee
</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/25/03 5:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2032.topic&index=34>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Military</span><hr size=1> Going in with a degree can be both a good and a bad thing.  Sure, you could get a commission and go the Officer route, but most Officers have no idea of what it's like being enlisted, and will attempt and sometimes succeed in walking all over you.  Not many people really have that much respect for officers either, at least not until they make Major.<br>
<br>
Officer life is very political.  If you can't stand that, don't go the officer route.<br>
<br>
Generally though, going in with a degree will help you out in rank, so does any Junior ROTC experience.  Make sure you ask a lot of questions regarding your job choices and wants at MEPS, that's basically your last chance before you sign your name to the dotted line.<br>
<br>
But yeah, make the most of it.  You'll get to do something that many people never do, go places many never go.  Sure, there's a lot of downs to it, but there's also a lot of ups. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.salvasti.com/EQ/" target="top">Bryannae Salvasti</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
