</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elsbetsquishytoes>elsbet squishytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Grey</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/26/03 6:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2032.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Military</span><hr size=1> Now I grew up as an Air Force brat.  My old man was smart, back in 1968, he wasn't hacking college too well, and as an able bodied 19 year old, he knew the Marines were all about hiring guys like him.  Figuring his chances of getting drafted into the Army or Marines was about as good as finding a Vietnamese guy in Vietnam, he went down to the Air Force recruiter and signed up for duty as a bomb loader.  28 years my old man spent in the Air Force, and only at the very end of those years was he happy with his choice.  <br>
<br>
I remember him sitting me down on the couch when I was about 12, saying, look here kid, whatever you do, don't sign up for the military.  I took the ASVAB in my senior year of high school, it was a free day off of classes, and the Navy was all over me, since my area of knowledge was right up their alley, but pops talked me out of signing their papers.<br>
<br>
Then again, I have a cousin in the Marines that does pretty well playing the French horn.  He is in no danger of being shot.  Fine life for him, but I enjoy being my own person, and I'm disgruntled about the current administration's war policy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=themadhatter106>The Mad Hatter 10 6</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/26/03 7:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2032.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Military</span><hr size=1> I have been in the Air Force for 7 years... I STILL get recruitment letters from the Navy... they just can't get the hint LOL. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takkonsmakafu>Takkon Smakafu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/26/03 10:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2032.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Military</span><hr size=1> Two questions.  If I get veteran status in the army, do my guns fire red tracers?  And, when I get elite status, do I self heal?<br>
